    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka diesel price cut to Rs430 a litre, petrol at Rs450",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka has cut the price diesel  by 10 rupees to 430 rupees a litre while petrol 92-Octane remains at 450 rupees a litre, state-run Ceylon Petroleum Corporation said.",
        "Kerosene which is similar to Jet fuel is usually the most expensive to import, diesel next and petrol is the cheapest to import.",
        "However in Sri Lanka due to mis-pricing of diesel over petrol over many decades, the more polluting diesel is widely used for goods transport in particular. (Colombo/Aug02/2022)"
      ],
